{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold Developers More Accountable in New Builds to Help Protect Nature ",
        "additional_details": "The Government should:\r\n \r\n1. Require early ecological surveys that prioritise keeping habitats and natural features in place.\r\n \r\n2. Mandate sustainable drainage, wildlife features, and on-site green measures, with off-site credits only if demonstrably unavoidable.\r\n \r\n3. Create a national register of serious planning breaches, with extra scrutiny for repeat offenders.\r\n \r\nWe believe these reforms would reduce flood risk, save costs, reward responsible developers, and protect communities.",
        "background": "We believe major property developments must protect existing trees, hedgerows, ponds, meadows, and other natural features, and developers who break planning rules should be held more accountable.",
